		   <table class="mform"  border="0" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="0" width="100%">
		   <tr><td class="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform" valign="top">For newbie Paladins<br clear=all>
		   <span class="sm">Posted @ Thu, Jan 4th 4:37 PM2001 </span><span id="notbold">| <span class=sm>IP: Logged</span> | <a href="/db/classes.html?class=6&mid=9786261682532&post=1"><a class=sm href="/db/classes.html?class=6&mid=9786261682532&num=0&post=1&replyto=9786261682532"><img src=/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=11 width=17> Reply to this</a></a>    <a name=9786261682532></a></small></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <span id=>Anonymous</span></a><b><span id=></span></b>
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default [2.00]</nobr><br><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Anonymous&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>I started EQ recently and played a Half-elven Paladin with Mithaniel Marr as my patron God. I am now a Lvl 20 Paladin and this are some advice for fellow aspiring Paladins:<br><br>Lvl 1-8<br>Work on leveling. You are basically a Warrior without all the perks and hit points. And you won't be anything like a Paladin til you get your spells.<br><br>If you start in Freeport as I do - work in EC, WC, and North Ro. Do orcs and dervs in a group. Collect orc belts and derv rings for sale. When solo try bears and young kodiaks (if you can manage). Save up and get a magical weapon for those Willowisp. If you want to be an all-rounder with all the weapons, please practice now and max your weapons skills up if you can.<br><br>At lvl 6 you get bash. Put in a pt and watch it go up. Against fighter types, you can probably bash incriminately and hope you outdamage him. Against caster type though, you have to exercise some patience. Bash can stun and interrupt spell castings, so watch when a caster is about to cast spells (you know, the colourful thingys flow out of their hands) and BASH. If you're good you'll see something like Caster X's spell casting is interrupted. You never will know what is to come but hey I'm sure you don't want to find out either.<br><br>Lvl 9 - 15<br>At lvl 9 you will get your 1st line of spells namely, Minor Healing; Spook the Dead; Flash of Light; Courage; True North; Yaulp and Cure Poison.<br><br>Put a point in your spell skills and watch them go up with use. Same as Med when you get it.<br><br>The spells you'll use most in combat is Yaulp and Flash of Light. Yaulp gives you +10 str buff and some minor AC buff for a short time (10 secs or so) and takes a short time to cast, so use it often no theres no harm to it. <br><br>Flash of Light (FOL) takes longer to cast but please don't underestimate its use. It took me some time but eventually I found that FOL could be a life saver sometimes. Aside from blinding your foes during combat, it can act as fear too. While we don't get root til 22, FOL can fill in the gap. When you are low in HP, flash your foe and step away from them to a distance. They'll start to run away from you. Then cast Minor Healing and heal up but they'll come running back to you when the spell wears off. If you think you are overmatched, RUN, RUN, RUN. Save me Lay Hands and much grief this way. <br><br>Bad thing about FOL is that when your foes run away, they may bring back friends (especially lions, bears and willowisp)and you will have more troubles. Sometimes they'll run away and bumb into something that aggroes and kill them and your effort would be wasted. Whatever it is play it safe, when in doubt RUN and Lay Hands while running. Some guys (like me earlier on) use FOL for pulling...same disadvantages as outlined above, especially in a camp, more often than not you'll get a train attack and you will have to run and shout to notify others.<br><br>And please don't cast spells when you feel like it. Spells has casting time and certain spells you just can't cast in time during combat without interruption. Watch your opponent fight. We usually get interruption when we got hurt during combat, immediately once your foe made his swing of weapon/swipe of paw/lurching to bite or whatever, regardless of whether you are hurt, if you want to cast any spells-its now!! Don't be impatient and cast your spells whenever you want to, you'll safe yourself some frustration this way.<br><br>At this stage go to WC and North Ro more often than not. Venture to Oasis and Befallen for some variety if you want.<br><br>At lvl 15 you will get Lull, Light Healing, Sense the Dead, Cure Disease, Holy Armor, Ward Undead. <br><br>Lull is great when you are working alone vs a camp. Note that lull usually work on those enemies that con blue and below to you. I find that more often than not black and yellow resist my spells and instead of being less aggressive, they come running in glee to spill my guts.<br><br>Lull with Ward Undead and you can probably work a Undead camp alone and pick em out one by one. With a magical weapon you can probably solo a ghoul and at some risk I would say.<br><br>Buff up before you step into combat. You need all the help you can get.<br><br>Lvl 16-20<br>After lvl 15 I seldom fight in EC, WC and North Ro. Oasis is still good though. I started going to the Karanas (North, South, East but not West never hunt in West yet) after lvl 15. East Karana is good XP but quite horrible loot. But if you're a tailor the spiders are very good opportunity to stock up on swatches and its Lion land there (for cat pelts). The bandits you can kill them for their sashes to bring back to Qeynos for a bronze weapon and XP<br><br>North Karana are bandits and beetles. South Karana is when you are in your 18-20 (and above), and get a group there when you go in at this stage.<br><br>If you can get a group go fight Orcs and Gnolls in High Hold, who knows you may get your PGT and CDS there. If you dunno whats a PGT and CDS, go surf somemore :)<br><br>Well this is my 2 coppers worth of information. It may not all be correct, please feel free to clear up any of my pts if you know better or can give better suggestions. <br><br>Lets help those newbie Paladins out there, Norrath need us Holy Warriors to be strong and able. <br><br>DS<br>Drinal Server<br>Lvl 20 Paladin of Mithaniel Marr<br><br></p></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >0 Replies</td></tr></table></td></tr></table><tr><td class=mhback align=right><span class=mh id=fs8><a class=mh href=/db/classes.html?class=6><img src=/shared/root_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Up" width=17 height=11> Thread Index</a> |  <a class=mh href=/db/classes.html?class=6&post=1><img src=/shared/new_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="New" width=17 height=11> New Subject</a> | <a class=mh href=/db/classes.html?class=6&mid=9786261682532&num=0&post=1&mid=9786261682532><img src=/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Reply" width=17 height=11> Reply to Thread</a></span></td></tr><tr><td><table width="100%" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" class="mform"><tr><td id="fs8">0 Posts [ <a href="/fsearch.html?base=class6">Search Forums</a> ]</nobr></td></tr></table>&nbsp;</td></tr>
